4681 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4682 /// \brief Reset offset and StremerInfo information from this branch.
4683 /// \param[in] recurse When true call ResetInitInfo on all subbranches.
4684 ///
4685 
4686 void TBranchElement::ResetInitInfo(Bool_t recurse)
4687 {
4688  fInfo = nullptr;
4689  fInit = kFALSE;
4690  fInitOffsets = kFALSE;
4691  fCurrentClass = nullptr;
4692  delete fReadActionSequence;
4693  fReadActionSequence = nullptr;
4694  delete fFillActionSequence;
4695  fFillActionSequence = nullptr;
4696 
4697  if (recurse) {
4698  Int_t nbranches = fBranches.GetEntriesFast();
4699  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nbranches; ++i) {
4700  TBranchElement *sub = (TBranchElement*) fBranches[i];
4701  sub->ResetInitInfo(kTRUE);
4702  }
4703  }
4704 }
4705 
4706 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4707 /// Point this branch at an object.
4708 ///
4709 /// For a sub-branch, addr is a pointer to the branch object.
4710 ///
4711 /// For a top-level branch the meaning of addr is as follows:
4712 ///
4713 /// If addr is zero, then we allocate a branch object
4714 /// internally and the branch is the owner of the allocated
4715 /// object, not the caller. However the caller may obtain
4716 /// a pointer to the branch object with GetObject().
4717 /// The pointer is reset to zero (nullptr) when the relevant
4718 /// branch object is destroyed.
4719 ///
4720 /// Example:
4721 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4722 /// branch->SetAddress(0);
4723 /// Event* event = branch->GetObject();
4724 /// ... Do some work.
4725 /// ~~~
4726 /// If addr is not zero, but the pointer addr points at is
4727 /// zero, then we allocate a branch object and set the passed
4728 /// pointer to point at the allocated object. The caller
4729 /// owns the allocated object and is responsible for deleting
4730 /// it when it is no longer needed.
4731 ///
4732 /// Example:
4733 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4734 /// Event* event = 0;
4735 /// branch->SetAddress(&event);
4736 /// ... Do some work.
4737 /// delete event;
4738 /// event = 0;
4739 /// ~~~
4740 /// If addr is not zero and the pointer addr points at is
4741 /// also not zero, then the caller has allocated a branch
4742 /// object and is asking us to use it. The caller owns it
4743 /// and must delete it when it is no longer needed.
4744 ///
4745 /// Example:
4746 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4747 /// Event* event = new Event();
4748 /// branch->SetAddress(&event);
4749 /// ... Do some work.
4750 /// delete event;
4751 /// event = 0;
4752 /// ~~~
4753 /// These rules affect users of TTree::Branch(),
4754 /// TTree::SetBranchAddress(), and TChain::SetBranchAddress()
4755 /// as well because those routines call this one.
4756 ///
4757 /// An example of a tree with branches with objects allocated
4758 /// and owned by us:
4759 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4760 /// TFile* f1 = new TFile("myfile_original.root");
4761 /// TTree* t1 = (TTree*) f->Get("MyTree");
4762 /// TFile* f2 = new TFile("myfile_copy.root", "recreate");
4763 /// TTree* t2 = t1->Clone(0);
4764 /// for (Int_t i = 0; i < 10; ++i) {
4765 /// t1->GetEntry(i);
4766 /// t2->Fill();
4767 /// }
4768 /// t2->Write()
4769 /// delete f2;
4770 /// f2 = 0;
4771 /// delete f1;
4772 /// f1 = 0;
4773 /// ~~~
4774 /// An example of a branch with an object allocated by us,
4775 /// but owned by the caller:
4776 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4777 /// TFile* f = new TFile("myfile.root", "recreate");
4778 /// TTree* t = new TTree("t", "A test tree.")
4779 /// Event* event = 0;
4780 /// TBranchElement* br = t->Branch("event.", &event);
4781 /// for (Int_t i = 0; i < 10; ++i) {
4782 /// ... Fill event with meaningful data in some way.
4783 /// t->Fill();
4784 /// }
4785 /// t->Write();
4786 /// delete event;
4787 /// event = 0;
4788 /// delete f;
4789 /// f = 0;
4790 /// ~~~
4791 /// Notice that the only difference between this example
4792 /// and the following example is that the event pointer
4793 /// is zero when the branch is created.
4794 ///
4795 /// An example of a branch with an object allocated and
4796 /// owned by the caller:
4797 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4798 /// TFile* f = new TFile("myfile.root", "recreate");
4799 /// TTree* t = new TTree("t", "A test tree.")
4800 /// Event* event = new Event();
4801 /// TBranchElement* br = t->Branch("event.", &event);
4802 /// for (Int_t i = 0; i < 10; ++i) {
4803 /// ... Fill event with meaningful data in some way.
4804 /// t->Fill();
4805 /// }
4806 /// t->Write();
4807 /// delete event;
4808 /// event = 0;
4809 /// delete f;
4810 /// f = 0;
4811 /// ~~~
4812 /// If AutoDelete is on (see TBranch::SetAutoDelete),
4813 /// the top level objet will be deleted and recreate
4814 /// each time an entry is read, whether or not the
4815 /// TTree owns the object.
4816 
4817 void TBranchElement::SetAddress(void* addr)
4818 {
4819  //
4820  // Don't bother if we are disabled.
4821  //
4822 
4823  if (TestBit(kDoNotProcess)) {
4824  return;
4825  }
4826 
4827  //
4828  // FIXME: When would this happen?
4829  //
4830 
4831  if (fType < -1) {
4832  return;
4833  }
4834 
4835  //
4836  // Special case when called from code generated by TTree::MakeClass.
4837  //
4838 
4839  if (Long_t(addr) == -1) {
4840  // FIXME: Do we have to release an object here?
4841  // ReleaseObject();
4842  fAddress = (char*) -1;
4843  fObject = (char*) -1;
4844  ResetBit(kDeleteObject);
4845  return;
4846  }
4847 
4848  //
4849  // Reset last read entry number, we have a new user object now.
4850  //
4851 
4852  fReadEntry = -1;
4853 
4854  //
4855  // Make sure our branch class is instantiated.
4856  //
4857  TClass* clOfBranch = fBranchClass.GetClass();
4858  if( fTargetClass.GetClassName()[0] ) {
4859  clOfBranch = fTargetClass;
4860  }
4861 
4862  //
4863  // Try to build the streamer info.
4864  //
4865 
4866  TStreamerInfo *info = GetInfoImp();
4867 
4868  // FIXME: Warn about failure to get the streamer info here?
4869 
4870  //
4871  // We may have allocated an object last time we were called.
4872  //
4873 
4874  if (fObject && TestBit(kDeleteObject)){
4875  ReleaseObject();
4876  }
4877 
4878  //
4879  // Remember the pointer to the pointer to our object.
4880  //
4881 
4882  fAddress = (char*) addr;
4883  if (fAddress != (char*)(&fObject)) {
4884  fObject = 0;
4885  }
4886  ResetBit(kDeleteObject);
4887 
4888  //
4889  // Do special stuff if we got called from a MakeClass class.
4890  // Allow sub-branches to have independently set addresses.
4891  //
4892 
4893  if (TestBit(kDecomposedObj)) {
4894  if (fID > -1) {
4895  // We are *not* a top-level branch.
4896  if (!info) {
4897  // No streamer info, give up.
4898  // FIXME: We should have an error message here.
4899  fObject = fAddress;
4900  } else {
4901  // Compensate for the fact that the i/o routines
4902  // will add the streamer offset to the address.
4903  fObject = fAddress - info->TStreamerInfo::GetElementOffset(fID);
4904  }
4905  return;
4906  }
4907  }
4908 
4909  //
4910  // Check whether the container type is still the same
4911  // to support schema evolution; what is written on the file
4912  // may no longer match the class code which is loaded.
4913  //
4914 
4915  if (fType == 3) {
4916  // split TClonesArray, counter/master branch.
4917  TClass* clm = fClonesClass;
4918  if (clm) {
4919  // In case clm derives from an abstract class.
4920  clm->BuildRealData();
4921  clm->GetStreamerInfo();
4922  }
4923  TClass* newType = GetCurrentClass();
4924  if (newType && (newType != TClonesArray::Class())) {
4925  // The data type of the container has changed.
4926  //
4927  // Let's check if it is a compatible type:
4928  Bool_t matched = kFALSE;
4929  if (newType->GetCollectionProxy()) {
4930  TClass *content = newType->GetCollectionProxy()->GetValueClass();
4931  if (clm == content) {
4932  matched = kTRUE;
4933  } else {
4934  Warning("SetAddress", "The type of %s was changed from TClonesArray to %s but the content do not match (was %s)!", GetName(), newType->GetName(), GetClonesName());
4935  }
4936  } else {
4937  Warning("SetAddress", "The type of the %s was changed from TClonesArray to %s but we do not have a TVirtualCollectionProxy for that container type!", GetName(), newType->GetName());
4938  }
4939  if (matched) {
4940  // Change from 3/31 to 4/41
4941  SetType(4);
4942  // Set the proxy.
4943  fSTLtype = newType->GetCollectionType();
4944  fCollProxy = newType->GetCollectionProxy()->Generate();
4945 
4946  SwitchContainer(GetListOfBranches());
4947  SetReadLeavesPtr();
4948  SetFillLeavesPtr();
4949 
4950  if(fSTLtype != ROOT::kSTLvector && fCollProxy->HasPointers() && fSplitLevel > TTree::kSplitCollectionOfPointers ) {
4951  fPtrIterators = new TVirtualCollectionPtrIterators(fCollProxy);
4952  } else if (fCollProxy->GetProperties() & TVirtualCollectionProxy::kIsAssociative) {
4953  fWriteIterators = new TVirtualCollectionIterators(fCollProxy,kFALSE);
4954  fIterators = new TVirtualCollectionIterators(fCollProxy);
4955  } else {
4956  fIterators = new TVirtualCollectionIterators(fCollProxy);
4957  }
4958  } else {
4959  // FIXME: Must maintain fObject here as well.
4960  fAddress = 0;
4961  }
4962  }
4963  } else if (fType == 4) {
4964  // split STL container, counter/master branch.
4965  TClass* newType = GetCurrentClass();
4966  if (newType && (newType != GetCollectionProxy()->GetCollectionClass())) {
4967  // Let's check if it is a compatible type:
4968  TVirtualCollectionProxy* newProxy = newType->GetCollectionProxy();
4969  TVirtualCollectionProxy* oldProxy = GetCollectionProxy();
4970  if (newProxy && (oldProxy->GetValueClass() == newProxy->GetValueClass()) && ((!oldProxy->GetValueClass() && (oldProxy->GetType() == newProxy->GetType())) || (oldProxy->GetValueClass() && (oldProxy->HasPointers() == newProxy->HasPointers())))) {
4971  delete fCollProxy;
4972  Int_t nbranches = GetListOfBranches()->GetEntries();
4973  fCollProxy = newType->GetCollectionProxy()->Generate();
4974  fSTLtype = fCollProxy->GetCollectionType();
4975  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nbranches; ++i) {
4976  TBranchElement* br = (TBranchElement*) GetListOfBranches()->UncheckedAt(i);
4977  br->fCollProxy = 0;
4978  if (br->fReadActionSequence) {
4979  br->SetReadActionSequence();
4980  }
4981  if (br->fFillActionSequence) {
4982  br->SetFillActionSequence();
4983  }
4984  }
4985  SetReadActionSequence();
4986  SetFillActionSequence();
4987  SetReadLeavesPtr();
4988  SetFillLeavesPtr();
4989  delete fIterators;
4990  delete fPtrIterators;
4991  if(fSTLtype != ROOT::kSTLvector && fCollProxy->HasPointers() && fSplitLevel > TTree::kSplitCollectionOfPointers ) {
4992  fPtrIterators = new TVirtualCollectionPtrIterators(fCollProxy);
4993  } else if (fCollProxy->GetProperties() & TVirtualCollectionProxy::kIsAssociative) {
4994  fWriteIterators = new TVirtualCollectionIterators(fCollProxy,kFALSE);
4995  fIterators = new TVirtualCollectionIterators(fCollProxy);
4996  } else {
4997  fIterators = new TVirtualCollectionIterators(fCollProxy);
4998  }
4999  }
5000  else if (newProxy && (oldProxy->HasPointers() == newProxy->HasPointers()) && (oldProxy->GetValueClass()!=0) && (newProxy->GetValueClass()!=0)) {
5001  // Let see if there is a rule to convert the content of the collection into each other.
5002  if (newType->GetSchemaRules()->HasRuleWithSourceClass( oldProxy->GetCollectionClass()->GetName())) {
5003  TClass *oldValueClass = oldProxy->GetValueClass();
5004  delete fCollProxy;
5005  Int_t nbranches = GetListOfBranches()->GetEntries();
5006  fCollProxy = newType->GetCollectionProxy()->Generate();
5007  fSTLtype = fCollProxy->GetCollectionType();
5008  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nbranches; ++i) {
5009  TBranchElement* br = (TBranchElement*) GetListOfBranches()->UncheckedAt(i);
5010  br->fCollProxy = 0;
5011  if (br->fBranchClass == oldValueClass) {
5012  br->SetTargetClass(fCollProxy->GetValueClass()->GetName());
5013  }
5014  if (br->fReadActionSequence) {
5015  br->SetReadActionSequence();
5016  }
5017  if (br->fFillActionSequence) {
5018  br->SetFillActionSequence();
5019  }
5020  }
5021  SetReadActionSequence();
5022  SetFillActionSequence();
5023  SetReadLeavesPtr();
5024  SetFillLeavesPtr();
5025  delete fIterators;
5026  delete fPtrIterators;
5027  if(fSTLtype != ROOT::kSTLvector && fCollProxy->HasPointers() && fSplitLevel > TTree::kSplitCollectionOfPointers ) {
5028  fPtrIterators = new TVirtualCollectionPtrIterators(fCollProxy);
5029  } else if (fCollProxy->GetProperties() & TVirtualCollectionProxy::kIsAssociative) {
5030  fWriteIterators = new TVirtualCollectionIterators(fCollProxy,kFALSE);
5031  fIterators = new TVirtualCollectionIterators(fCollProxy);
5032  } else {
5033  fIterators = new TVirtualCollectionIterators(fCollProxy);
5034  }
5035  } else {
5036  Error("SetAddress","For %s, we can not convert %s into %s\n",
5037  GetName(),oldProxy->GetCollectionClass()->GetName(),newType->GetName());
5038  fAddress = 0;
5039  fObject = 0;
5040  return;
5041  }
5042  }
5043  else if ((newType == TClonesArray::Class()) && (oldProxy->GetValueClass() && !oldProxy->HasPointers() && oldProxy->GetValueClass()->IsTObject()))
5044  {
5045  // The new collection and the old collection are not compatible,
5046  // we cannot use the new collection to read the data.
5047  // Actually we could check if the new collection is a
5048  // compatible ROOT collection.
5049 
5050  // We cannot insure that the TClonesArray is set for the
5051  // proper class (oldProxy->GetValueClass()), so we assume that
5052  // the transformation was done properly by the class designer.
5053 
5054  // Change from 4/41 to 3/31
5055  SetType(3);
5056  // Reset the proxy.
5057  fSTLtype = kNone;
5058  switch(fStreamerType) {
5059  case TVirtualStreamerInfo::kAny:
5060  case TVirtualStreamerInfo::kSTL:
5061  fStreamerType = TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObject;
5062  break;
5063  case TVirtualStreamerInfo::kAnyp:
5064  case TVirtualStreamerInfo::kSTLp:
5065  fStreamerType = TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObjectp;
5066  break;
5067  case TVirtualStreamerInfo::kAnyP:
5068  fStreamerType = TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObjectP;
5069  break;
5070  }
5071  fClonesClass = oldProxy->GetValueClass();
5072  fClonesName = fClonesClass->GetName();
5073  delete fCollProxy;
5074  fCollProxy = 0;
5075  TClass* clm = fClonesClass;
5076  if (clm) {
5077  clm->BuildRealData(); //just in case clm derives from an abstract class
5078  clm->GetStreamerInfo();
5079  }
5080  SwitchContainer(GetListOfBranches());
5081  SetReadLeavesPtr();
5082  SetFillLeavesPtr();
5083  delete fIterators;
5084  fIterators = 0;
5085  delete fPtrIterators;
5086  fPtrIterators =0;
5087  } else {
5088  // FIXME: We must maintain fObject here as well.
5089  Error("SetAddress","For %s can not convert %s into %s\n",GetName(),GetCurrentClass()->GetName(),newType->GetName());
5090  fAddress = 0;
5091  return;
5092  }
5093  } else {
5094  if (!fIterators && !fPtrIterators) {
5095  if(fSTLtype != ROOT::kSTLvector && GetCollectionProxy()->HasPointers() && fSplitLevel > TTree::kSplitCollectionOfPointers ) {
5096  fPtrIterators = new TVirtualCollectionPtrIterators(GetCollectionProxy());
5097  } else if (fCollProxy->GetProperties() & TVirtualCollectionProxy::kIsAssociative) {
5098  fWriteIterators = new TVirtualCollectionIterators(fCollProxy,kFALSE);
5099  fIterators = new TVirtualCollectionIterators(fCollProxy);
5100  } else {
5101  fIterators = new TVirtualCollectionIterators(GetCollectionProxy());
5102  }
5103  }
5104  }
5105  }
5106 
5107  //
5108  // Establish the semantics of fObject and fAddress.
5109  //
5110  // Top-level branch:
5111  // fObject is a ptr to the object,
5112  // fAddress is a ptr to a pointer to the object.
5113  //
5114  // Sub-branch:
5115  // fObject is a ptr to the object,
5116  // fAddress is the same as fObject.
5117  //
5118  //
5119  // There are special cases for TClonesArray and STL containers.
5120  // If there is no user-provided object, we allocate one. We must
5121  // also initialize any STL container proxy.
5122  //
5123 
5124  if (fType == 3) {
5125  // -- We are a TClonesArray master branch.
5126  if (fAddress) {
5127  // -- We have been given a non-zero address, allocate if necessary.
5128  if (fStreamerType == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObject) {
5129  // -- We are *not* a top-level branch and we are *not* a pointer to a TClonesArray.
5130  // Case of an embedded TClonesArray.
5131  fObject = fAddress;
5132  // Check if it has already been properly built.
5133  TClonesArray* clones = (TClonesArray*) fObject;
5134  if (!clones->GetClass()) {
5135  new(fObject) TClonesArray(fClonesClass);
5136  }
5137  } else {
5138  // -- We are either a top-level branch or we are a subbranch which is a pointer to a TClonesArray.
5139  // Streamer type should be -1 (for a top-level branch) or kObject(p|P) here.
5140  if ((fStreamerType != -1) &&
5141  (fStreamerType != TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObjectp) &&
5142  (fStreamerType != TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObjectP)) {
5143  Error("SetAddress", "TClonesArray with fStreamerType: %d", fStreamerType);
5144  } else if (fStreamerType == -1) {
5145  // -- We are a top-level branch.
5146  TClonesArray** pp = (TClonesArray**) fAddress;
5147  if (!*pp) {
5148  // -- Caller wants us to allocate the clones array, but they will own it.
5149  *pp = new TClonesArray(fClonesClass);
5150  }
5151  fObject = (char*) *pp;
5152  } else {
5153  // -- We are a pointer to a TClonesArray.
5154  // Note: We do this so that the default constructor,
5155  // or the i/o constructor can be lazy.
5156  TClonesArray** pp = (TClonesArray**) fAddress;
5157  if (!*pp) {
5158  // -- Caller wants us to allocate the clones array, but they will own it.
5159  *pp = new TClonesArray(fClonesClass);
5160  }
5161  fObject = (char*) *pp;
5162  }
5163  }
5164  } else {
5165  // -- We have been given a zero address, allocate for top-level only.
5166  if (fStreamerType == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObject) {
5167  // -- We are *not* a top-level branch and we are *not* a pointer to a TClonesArray.
5168  // Case of an embedded TClonesArray.
5169  Error("SetAddress", "Embedded TClonesArray given a zero address for branch '%s'", GetName());
5170  } else {
5171  // -- We are either a top-level branch or we are a subbranch which is a pointer to a TClonesArray.
5172  // Streamer type should be -1 (for a top-level branch) or kObject(p|P) here.
5173  if ((fStreamerType != -1) &&
5174  (fStreamerType != TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObjectp) &&
5175  (fStreamerType != TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObjectP)) {
5176  Error("SetAddress", "TClonesArray with fStreamerType: %d", fStreamerType);
5177  } else if (fStreamerType == -1) {
5178  // -- We are a top-level branch.
5179  // Idea: Consider making a zero address not allocate.
5180  SetBit(kDeleteObject);
5181  fObject = (char*) new TClonesArray(fClonesClass);
5182  fAddress = (char*) &fObject;
5183  } else {
5184  // -- We are a sub-branch which is a pointer to a TClonesArray.
5185  Error("SetAddress", "Embedded pointer to a TClonesArray given a zero address for branch '%s'", GetName());
5186  }
5187  }
5188  }
5189  } else if (fType == 4) {
5190  // -- We are an STL container master branch.
5191  //
5192  // Initialize fCollProxy.
5193  TVirtualCollectionProxy* proxy = GetCollectionProxy();
5194  if (fAddress) {
5195  // -- We have been given a non-zero address, allocate if necessary.
5196  if ((fStreamerType == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObject) ||
5197  (fStreamerType == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kAny) ||
5198  (fStreamerType == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kSTL)) {
5199  // We are *not* a top-level branch and we are *not* a pointer to an STL container.
5200  // Case of an embedded STL container.
5201  // Note: We test for the kObject and kAny types to support
5202  // the (unwise) choice of inheriting from an STL container.
5203  fObject = fAddress;
5204  } else {
5205  // We are either a top-level branch or subbranch which is a pointer to an STL container.
5206  // Streamer type should be -1 (for a top-level branch) or kSTLp here.
5207  if ((fStreamerType != -1) && (fStreamerType != TVirtualStreamerInfo::kSTLp)) {
5208  Error("SetAddress", "STL container with fStreamerType: %d", fStreamerType);
5209  } else if (fStreamerType == -1) {
5210  // -- We are a top-level branch.
5211  void** pp = (void**) fAddress;
5212  if (!*pp) {
5213  // -- Caller wants us to allocate the STL container, but they will own it.
5214  *pp = proxy->New();
5215  if (!(*pp)) {
5216  Error("SetAddress", "Failed to allocate STL container for branch '%s'", GetName());
5217  // FIXME: Should we do this? Lots of other code wants
5218  // fAddress to be zero if no fObject, but is
5219  // that a good thing?
5220  fAddress = 0;
5221  }
5222  }
5223  fObject = (char*) *pp;
5224  } else {
5225  // -- We are a pointer to an STL container.
5226  // Note: We do this so that the default constructor,
5227  // or the i/o constructor can be lazy.
5228  void** pp = (void**) fAddress;
5229  if (!*pp) {
5230  // -- Caller wants us to allocate the STL container, but they will own it.
5231  *pp = proxy->New();
5232  if (!(*pp)) {
5233  Error("SetAddress", "Failed to allocate STL container for branch '%s'", GetName());
5234  // FIXME: Should we do this? Lots of other code wants
5235  // fAddress to be zero if no fObject, but is
5236  // that a good thing?
5237  fAddress = 0;
5238  }
5239  }
5240  fObject = (char*) *pp;
5241  }
5242  }
5243  } else {
5244  // -- We have been given a zero address, allocate for top-level only.
5245  if ((fStreamerType == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObject) ||
5246  (fStreamerType == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kAny) ||
5247  (fStreamerType == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kSTL)) {
5248  // We are *not* a top-level branch and we are *not* a pointer to an STL container.
5249  // Case of an embedded STL container.
5250  // Note: We test for the kObject and kAny types to support
5251  // the (unwise) choice of inheriting from an STL container.
5252  Error("SetAddress", "Embedded STL container given a zero address for branch '%s'", GetName());
5253  } else {
5254  // We are either a top-level branch or sub-branch which is a pointer to an STL container.
5255  // Streamer type should be -1 (for a top-level branch) or kSTLp here.
5256  if ((fStreamerType != -1) && (fStreamerType != TVirtualStreamerInfo::kSTLp)) {
5257  Error("SetAddress", "STL container with fStreamerType: %d", fStreamerType);
5258  } else if (fStreamerType == -1) {
5259  // -- We are a top-level branch, allocate.
5260  SetBit(kDeleteObject);
5261  fObject = (char*) proxy->New();
5262  if (fObject) {
5263  fAddress = (char*) &fObject;
5264  } else {
5265  Error("SetAddress", "Failed to allocate STL container for branch '%s'", GetName());
5266  // FIXME: Should we do this? Lots of other code wants
5267  // fAddress to be zero if no fObject, but is
5268  // that a good thing?
5269  fAddress = 0;
5270  }
5271  } else {
5272  // -- We are a sub-branch which is a pointer to an STL container.
5273  Error("SetAddress", "Embedded pointer to an STL container given a zero address for branch '%s'", GetName());
5274  }
5275  }
5276  }
5277  } else if (fType == 41) {
5278  // -- We are an STL container sub-branch.
5279  // Initialize fCollProxy.
5280  GetCollectionProxy();
5281  // We are not at top-level branch.
5282  fObject = fAddress;
5283  } else if (fID < 0) {
5284  // -- We are a top-level branch.
5285  char** pp = (char**) fAddress;
5286  if (pp && *pp) {
5287  // -- Caller provided an i/o buffer for us to use.
5288  fObject = *pp;
5289  } else {
5290  // -- Caller did not provide an i/o buffer for us to use, we must make one for ourselves.
5291  if (clOfBranch) {
5292  if (!pp) {
5293  // -- Caller wants us to own the object.
5294  SetBit(kDeleteObject);
5295  }
5296  fObject = (char*) clOfBranch->New();
5297  if (pp) {
5298  *pp = fObject;
5299  } else {
5300  fAddress = (char*) &fObject;
5301  }
5302  } else {
5303  Error("SetAddress", "I have no TClass for branch %s, so I cannot allocate an I/O buffer!", GetName());
5304  if (pp) {
5305  fObject = 0;
5306  *pp = 0;
5307  }
5308  }
5309  }
5310  } else {
5311  // -- We are *not* a top-level branch.
5312  fObject = fAddress;
5313  }
5314 
5315  if (!info) {
5316  // FIXME: We need and error message here, no streamer info, so cannot set offsets.
5317  return;
5318  }
5319 
5320  // We do this only once because it depends only on
5321  // the type of our object, not on its address.
5322  if (!fInitOffsets) {
5323  InitializeOffsets();
5324  }
5325 
5326  // We are split, recurse down to our sub-branches.
5327  //
5328  // FIXME: This is a tail recursion, we burn stack.
5329  Int_t nbranches = fBranches.GetEntriesFast();
5330  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nbranches; ++i) {
5331  TBranch* abranch = (TBranch*) fBranches.UncheckedAt(i);
5332  // FIXME: This is a tail recursion!
5333  if (fBranchOffset[i] != TStreamerInfo::kMissing) {
5334  abranch->SetAddress(fObject + fBranchOffset[i]);
5335  abranch->SetBit(kAddressSet);
5336  } else {
5337  // When the member is missing, just leave the address alone
5338  // (since setting explicitly to 0 would trigger error/warning
5339  // messages).
5340  // abranch->SetAddress(0);
5341  abranch->SetBit(kAddressSet);
5342  }
5343  }
5344 }
5345 
5346 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5347 /// Reset the basket size for all sub-branches of this branch element.
5348 
5349 void TBranchElement::SetBasketSize(Int_t buffsize)
5350 {
5351  TBranch::SetBasketSize(buffsize);
5352  Int_t nbranches = fBranches.GetEntriesFast();
5353  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nbranches; ++i) {
5354  TBranch* branch = (TBranch*) fBranches[i];
5355  branch->SetBasketSize(fBasketSize);
5356  }
5357 }
5358 
5359 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5360 /// Set the branch counter for this branch.
5361 
5362 void TBranchElement::SetBranchCount(TBranchElement* brOfCounter)
5363 {
5364  fBranchCount = brOfCounter;
5365  if (fBranchCount==0) return;
5366 
5367  TLeafElement* leafOfCounter = (TLeafElement*) brOfCounter->GetListOfLeaves()->At(0);
5368  TLeafElement* leaf = (TLeafElement*) GetListOfLeaves()->At(0);
5369  if (leafOfCounter && leaf) {
5370  leaf->SetLeafCount(leafOfCounter);
5371  } else {
5372  if (!leafOfCounter) {
5373  Warning("SetBranchCount", "Counter branch %s for branch %s has no leaves!", brOfCounter->GetName(), GetName());
5374  }
5375  if (!leaf) {
5376  Warning("SetBranchCount", "Branch %s has no leaves!", GetName());
5377  }
5378  }
5379 }
5380 
5381 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5382 /// Set the branch in a mode where the object are decomposed
5383 /// (Also known as MakeClass mode).
5384 /// Return whether the setting was possible (it is not possible for
5385 /// TBranch and TBranchObject).
5386 
5387 Bool_t TBranchElement::SetMakeClass(Bool_t decomposeObj)
5388 {
5389  if (decomposeObj)
5390  SetBit(kDecomposedObj); // Same as SetBit(kMakeClass)
5391  else
5392  ResetBit(kDecomposedObj);
5393 
5394  Int_t nbranches = fBranches.GetEntriesFast();
5395  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nbranches; ++i) {
5396  TBranchElement* branch = (TBranchElement*) fBranches[i];
5397  branch->SetMakeClass(decomposeObj);
5398  }
5399  SetReadLeavesPtr();
5400  SetFillLeavesPtr();
5401 
5402  return kTRUE;
5403 }

5405 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5406 /// Set object this branch is pointing to.
5407 
5408 void TBranchElement::SetObject(void* obj)
5409 {
5410  if (TestBit(kDoNotProcess)) {
5411  return;
5412  }
5413  fObject = (char*)obj;
5414  SetAddress( &fObject );
5415 }
5416 
5417 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5418 /// Set offset of the object (to which the data member represented by this
5419 /// branch belongs) inside its containing object (if any).
5420 
5421 void TBranchElement::SetOffset(Int_t offset)
5422 {
5423  // We need to make sure that the Read and Write action's configuration
5424  // properly reflect this value.
5425 
5426  if (offset == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kMissing) {
5427  SetMissing();
5428  return;
5429  }
5430 
5431  if (fReadActionSequence) {
5432  fReadActionSequence->AddToOffset(offset - fOffset);
5433  }
5434  if (fFillActionSequence) {
5435  fFillActionSequence->AddToOffset(offset - fOffset);
5436  }
5437  fOffset = offset;
5438 }
5439 
5440 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5441 /// Set offset of the object (to which the data member represented by this
5442 /// branch belongs) inside its containing object (if any) to mark it as missing.
5443 
5444 void TBranchElement::SetMissing()
5445 {
5446  // We need to make sure that the Read and Write action's configuration
5447  // properly reflect this value.
5448 
5449  if (fReadActionSequence) {
5450  fReadActionSequence->SetMissing();
5451  }
5452  if (fFillActionSequence) {
5453  fFillActionSequence->SetMissing();
5454  }
5455  fOffset = TVirtualStreamerInfo::kMissing;
5456 }
5457 
5458 
5459 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5460 /// Set the sequence of actions needed to read the data out of the buffer.
5461 void TBranchElement::SetActionSequence(TClass *originalClass, TStreamerInfo *localInfo, TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::SequenceGetter_t create, TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence *&actionSequence)
5462 {
5463  // A 'split' node does not store data itself (it has not associated baskets)
5464  const bool isSplitNode = (fType == 3 || fType == 4 || fType == 2 || fType == 1 || (fType == 0 && fID == -2)) && !fBranches.IsEmpty();
5465 
5466  if (!isSplitNode) {
5467  fNewIDs.insert(fNewIDs.begin(),fID); // Include the main element in the sequence.
5468  }
5469 
5470  if (actionSequence) delete actionSequence;
5471  auto original = create(localInfo, GetCollectionProxy(), originalClass);
5472 
5473  actionSequence = original->CreateSubSequence(fNewIDs, fOffset, create);
5474 
5475  if (!isSplitNode)
5476  fNewIDs.erase(fNewIDs.begin());
5477 
5478  else if (fInitOffsets && fType != 3 && fType != 4) {
5479  // fObject has the address of the sub-object but the streamer action have
5480  // offset relative to the parent.
5481 
5482  // Note: We skipped this for the top node of split collection because the
5483  // sequence is about the content, we need to review what happens where an
5484  // action related to the collection itself will land.
5485  TBranchElement *parent = dynamic_cast<TBranchElement*>(GetMother()->GetSubBranch(this));
5486 
5487  auto index = parent->fBranches.IndexOf(this);
5488  if (index >= 0) {
5489  actionSequence->AddToOffset( - parent->fBranchOffset[index] );
5490  }
5491  } // else it will be done by InitOffsets
5492 }
5493 
5494 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5495 /// Set the sequence of actions needed to read the data out of the buffer.
5496 void TBranchElement::SetReadActionSequence()
5497 {
5498  if (fInfo == 0) {
5499  // We are called too soon. We will be called again by InitInfo
5500  return;
5501  }
5502 
5503  TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::SequenceGetter_t create = nullptr;
5504  TClass *originalClass = nullptr;
5505  TStreamerInfo *localInfo = fInfo;
5506  if (fType == 41) {
5507  if( fSplitLevel >= TTree::kSplitCollectionOfPointers && fBranchCount->fSTLtype == ROOT::kSTLvector) {
5508  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::ReadMemberWiseActionsCollectionGetter;
5509  } else {
5510  TVirtualStreamerInfo *info = GetInfoImp();
5511  if (GetParentClass() == info->GetClass()) {
5512  if( fTargetClass.GetClassName()[0] && fBranchClass != fTargetClass ) {
5513  originalClass = fBranchClass;
5514  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::ConversionReadMemberWiseActionsViaProxyGetter;
5515  } else {
5516  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::ReadMemberWiseActionsViaProxyGetter;
5517  }
5518  } else if (GetCollectionProxy()) {
5519  // Base class and embedded objects.
5520  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::ReadMemberWiseActionsCollectionCreator;
5521  }
5522  }
5523  } else if (fType == 31) {
5524  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::ReadMemberWiseActionsCollectionGetter;
5525  } else if (0<=fType && fType<=2) {
5526  // Note: this still requires the ObjectWise sequence to not be optimized!
5527  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::ReadMemberWiseActionsGetter;
5528  } else if ( fType == 4 && !fNewIDs.empty()) {
5529  localInfo = FindOnfileInfo(fClonesClass, fBranches);
5530  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::ReadMemberWiseActionsCollectionCreator;
5531  } else if ( fType == 3 && !fNewIDs.empty()) {
5532  localInfo = FindOnfileInfo(fClonesClass, fBranches);
5533  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::ReadMemberWiseActionsCollectionGetter;
5534  }
5535 
5536  if (create) {
5537  SetActionSequence(originalClass, localInfo, create, fReadActionSequence);
5538  }
5539 }
5540 
5541 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5542 /// Set the ReadLeaves pointer to execute the expected operations.
5543 
5544 void TBranchElement::SetReadLeavesPtr()
5545 {
5546  if (TestBit(kDecomposedObj)) {
5547  fReadLeaves = (ReadLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::ReadLeavesMakeClass;
5548  } else if (fType == 4) {
5549  fReadLeaves = (ReadLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::ReadLeavesCollection;
5550  } else if (fType == 41) {
5551  if( fSplitLevel >= TTree::kSplitCollectionOfPointers ) {
5552  if (fBranchCount->fSTLtype == ROOT::kSTLvector) {
5553  fReadLeaves = (ReadLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::ReadLeavesCollectionSplitVectorPtrMember;
5554  } else {
5555  fReadLeaves = (ReadLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::ReadLeavesCollectionSplitPtrMember;
5556  }
5557  } else {
5558  fReadLeaves = (ReadLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::ReadLeavesCollectionMember;
5559  }
5560  } else if (fType == 3) {
5561  fReadLeaves = (ReadLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::ReadLeavesClones;
5562  } else if (fType == 31) {
5563  fReadLeaves = (ReadLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::ReadLeavesClonesMember;
5564  } else if (fType < 0) {
5565  fReadLeaves = (ReadLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::ReadLeavesCustomStreamer;
5566  } else if (fType == 0 && fID == -1) {
5567  // top-level branch.
5568  Bool_t hasCustomStreamer = !fBranchClass.GetClass()->GetCollectionProxy() && (fBranchClass.GetClass()->GetStreamer() != 0 || fBranchClass.GetClass()->TestBit(TClass::kHasCustomStreamerMember));
5569  if (hasCustomStreamer) {
5570  // We are in the case where the object did *not* have a custom
5571  // Streamer when the TTree was written but now *does* have a custom
5572  // Streamer thus we must use it.
5573  fReadLeaves = (ReadLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::ReadLeavesCustomStreamer;
5574  } else {
5575  fReadLeaves = (ReadLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::ReadLeavesMember;
5576  }
5577  } else if (fType <= 2) {
5578  // split-class branch, base class branch or data member branch.
5579  if (fBranchCount) {
5580  fReadLeaves = (ReadLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::ReadLeavesMemberBranchCount;
5581  } else if (fStreamerType == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kCounter) {
5582  fReadLeaves = (ReadLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::ReadLeavesMemberCounter;
5583  } else {
5584  fReadLeaves = (ReadLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::ReadLeavesMember;
5585  }
5586  } else {
5587  Fatal("SetReadLeavePtr","Unexpected branch type %d for %s",fType,GetName());
5588  }
5589 
5590  SetReadActionSequence();
5591 }
5592 
5593 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5594 /// Set the sequence of actions needed to write the data out from the buffer.
5595 
5596 void TBranchElement::SetFillActionSequence()
5597 {
5598  if (fInfo == 0) {
5599  // We are called too soon. We will be called again by InitInfo
5600  return;
5601  }
5602 
5603  TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::SequenceGetter_t create = nullptr;
5604  TClass *originalClass = nullptr;
5605  TStreamerInfo *localInfo = fInfo;
5606  if (fType == 41) {
5607  if( fSplitLevel >= TTree::kSplitCollectionOfPointers && fBranchCount->fSTLtype == ROOT::kSTLvector) {
5608  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::WriteMemberWiseActionsCollectionGetter;
5609  } else {
5610  TVirtualStreamerInfo *info = GetInfoImp();
5611  if (GetParentClass() == info->GetClass()) {
5612  // if( fTargetClass.GetClassName()[0] && fBranchClass != fTargetClass ) {
5613  // originalClass = fBranchClass;
5614  // create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::ConversionWriteMemberWiseActionsViaProxyGetter;
5615  // } else {
5616  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::WriteMemberWiseActionsViaProxyGetter;
5617  // }
5618  } else if (GetCollectionProxy()) {
5619  // Base class and embedded objects.
5620  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::WriteMemberWiseActionsCollectionCreator;
5621  }
5622  }
5623  } else if (fType == 31) {
5624  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::WriteMemberWiseActionsCollectionGetter;
5625  } else if (0<=fType && fType<=2) {
5626  // Note: this still requires the ObjectWise sequence to not be optimized!
5627  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::WriteMemberWiseActionsGetter;
5628  } else if ( fType == 4 && !fNewIDs.empty()) {
5629  localInfo = FindOnfileInfo(fClonesClass, fBranches);
5630  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::WriteMemberWiseActionsCollectionCreator;
5631  } else if ( fType == 3 && !fNewIDs.empty()) {
5632  localInfo = FindOnfileInfo(fClonesClass, fBranches);
5633  create = TStreamerInfoActions::TActionSequence::WriteMemberWiseActionsCollectionGetter;
5634  }
5635 
5636  if (create) {
5637  SetActionSequence(originalClass, localInfo, create, fFillActionSequence);
5638  }
5639 }

5641 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5642 /// Set the FillLeaves pointer to execute the expected operations.
5643 
5644 void TBranchElement::SetFillLeavesPtr()
5645 {
5646  if (TestBit(kDecomposedObj) && ((fType==3)||(fType==31))) {
5647  fFillLeaves = (FillLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::FillLeavesMakeClass;
5648  } else if (fType == 4) {
5649  fFillLeaves = (FillLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::FillLeavesCollection;
5650  } else if (fType == 41) {
5651  if( fSplitLevel >= TTree::kSplitCollectionOfPointers ) {
5652  if (fBranchCount->fSTLtype == ROOT::kSTLvector) {
5653  fFillLeaves = (FillLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::FillLeavesCollectionSplitVectorPtrMember;
5654  } else {
5655  fFillLeaves = (FillLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::FillLeavesCollectionSplitPtrMember;
5656  }
5657  } else if (GetCollectionProxy()->GetProperties() & TVirtualCollectionProxy::kIsAssociative) {
5658  fFillLeaves = (FillLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::FillLeavesAssociativeCollectionMember;
5659  } else {
5660  fFillLeaves = (FillLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::FillLeavesCollectionMember;
5661  }
5662  } else if (fType == 3) {
5663  fFillLeaves = (FillLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::FillLeavesClones;
5664  } else if (fType == 31) {
5665  fFillLeaves = (FillLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::FillLeavesClonesMember;
5666  } else if (fType < 0) {
5667  fFillLeaves = (FillLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::FillLeavesCustomStreamer;
5668  } else if (fType <=2) {
5669  //split-class branch, base class branch, data member branch, or top-level branch.
5670  if (fBranchCount) {
5671  fFillLeaves = (FillLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::FillLeavesMemberBranchCount;
5672  } else if (fStreamerType == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kCounter) {
5673  fFillLeaves = (FillLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::FillLeavesMemberCounter;
5674  } else {
5675  fFillLeaves = (FillLeaves_t)&TBranchElement::FillLeavesMember;
5676  }
5677  } else {
5678  Fatal("SetFillLeavePtr","Unexpected branch type %d for %s",fType,GetName());
5679  }
5680 
5681  SetFillActionSequence();
5682 }
5683 
5684 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5685 /// Set the name of the class of the in-memory object into which the data will
5686 /// loaded.
5687 
5688 void TBranchElement::SetTargetClass(const char *name)
5689 {
5690  if (name == 0) return;
5691 
5692  if (strcmp(fTargetClass.GetClassName(),name) != 0 )
5693  {
5694  // We are changing target class, let's reset the meta information and
5695  // the sub-branches.
5696 
5697  ResetInitInfo(/*recurse=*/ kFALSE);
5698 
5699  Int_t nbranches = fBranches.GetEntriesFast();
5700  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nbranches; ++i) {
5701  TBranchElement *sub = (TBranchElement*) fBranches[i];
5702 
5703  if (sub->fTargetClass == fTargetClass ) {
5704  sub->SetTargetClass(name);
5705  } else {
5706  // Since the top level changes, the StreamerInfo (in particular for split collection)
5707  // may still need to change (and the info might be updated else (see for example SetAddress for the
5708  // the case fType 4/41)
5709  sub->ResetInitInfo(kTRUE);
5710  }
5711  if (sub->fParentClass == fTargetClass ) {
5712  sub->SetParentClass(TClass::GetClass(name));
5713  }
5714  }
5715  fTargetClass = name;
5716  }
5717 
5718 }
5719 
5720 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5721 /// If the branch address is not set, we set all addresses starting with
5722 /// the top level parent branch. This is required to be done in order for
5723 /// GetOffset to be correct and for GetEntry to run.
5724 
5725 void TBranchElement::SetupAddresses()
5726 {
5727  // Check to see if the user changed the branch address on us.
5728  ValidateAddress();
5729 
5730  if (fAddress || TestBit(kDecomposedObj)) {
5731  // -- Do nothing if already setup or if we are a MakeClass branch.
5732  return;
5733  }
5734  SetupAddressesImpl();
5735 }
5736 
5737 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5738 /// If the branch address is not set, we set all addresses starting with
5739 /// the top level parent branch. This is required to be done in order for
5740 /// GetOffset to be correct and for GetEntry to run.
5741 
5742 void TBranchElement::SetupAddressesImpl()
5743 {
5744  if (TestBit(kDoNotProcess|kAddressSet)) {
5745  // -- Do nothing if we have been told not to.
5746  // Or the data member in this branch is not longer part of the
5747  // parent's layout.
5748  return;
5749  }
5750 
5751  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
5752  // Check if we are splited STL collection of pointers
5753  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5754 
5755  if( fType == 41 && fSplitLevel >= TTree::kSplitCollectionOfPointers )
5756  {
5757  TBranchElement *parent = (TBranchElement *)GetMother()->GetSubBranch( this );
5758 
5759  // Make sure the StreamerInfo is loaded and initialized.
5760  GetInfoImp();
5761 
5762  if( !parent->GetAddress() )
5763  parent->SetAddress( 0 );
5764  return;
5765  }
5766 
5767  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
5768  // Any other case
5769  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5770 
5771  TBranchElement* mother = (TBranchElement*) GetMother();
5772  if (!mother) {
5773  return;
5774  }
5775  TClass* cl = TClass::GetClass(mother->GetClassName());
5776 
5777  // Make sure the StreamerInfo is loaded and initialized.
5778  GetInfoImp();
5779 
5780  if (!cl) {
5781  return;
5782  }
5783 
5784  if (!mother->GetAddress()) {
5785  // -- Our top-level branch has no address.
5786  Bool_t motherStatus = mother->TestBit(kDoNotProcess);
5787  mother->ResetBit(kDoNotProcess);
5788  // Note: This will allocate an object.
5789  mother->SetAddress(0);
5790  mother->SetBit(kDoNotProcess, motherStatus);
5791  }
5792 }
5793 
5794 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5795 /// Stream an object of class TBranchElement.
5796 
5797 void TBranchElement::Streamer(TBuffer& R__b)
5798 {
5799  if (R__b.IsReading()) {
5800  R__b.ReadClassBuffer(TBranchElement::Class(), this);
5801  fParentClass.SetName(fParentName);
5802  fBranchClass.SetName(fClassName);
5803  fTargetClass.SetName(fClassName);
5804  fClonesClass.SetName(fClonesName);
5805  // The fAddress and fObject data members are not persistent,
5806  // therefore we do not own anything.
5807  // Also clear the bit possibly set by the schema evolution.
5808  ResetBit(kDeleteObject|kCache|kOwnOnfileObj|kAddressSet|kDecomposedObj);
5809  // Fixup a case where the TLeafElement was missing
5810  if ((fType == 0) && (fLeaves.GetEntriesFast() == 0)) {
5811  TLeaf* leaf = new TLeafElement(this, GetTitle(), fID, fStreamerType);
5812  leaf->SetTitle(GetTitle());
5813  fNleaves = 1;
5814  fLeaves.Add(leaf);
5815  fTree->GetListOfLeaves()->Add(leaf);
5816  }
5817 
5818  // SetReadLeavesPtr();
5819  }
5820  else {
5821  TDirectory* dirsav = fDirectory;
5822  fDirectory = 0; // to avoid recursive calls
5823  {
5824  // Save class version.
5825  Int_t classVersion = fClassVersion;
5826  // Record only positive 'version number'
5827  if (fClassVersion < 0) {
5828  fClassVersion = -fClassVersion;
5829  }
5830  // TODO: Should we clear the kDeleteObject bit before writing?
5831  // If we did we would have to remember the old value and
5832  // put it back, we wouldn't want to forget that we owned
5833  // something just because we got written to disk.
5834  R__b.WriteClassBuffer(TBranchElement::Class(), this);
5835  // Restore class version.
5836  fClassVersion = classVersion;
5837  }
5838  //
5839  // Mark all streamer infos used by this branch element
5840  // to be written to our output file.
5841  //
5842  {
5843  R__b.ForceWriteInfo(GetInfoImp(), kTRUE);
5844  }
5845  //
5846  // If we are a clones array master branch, or an
5847  // STL container master branch, we must also mark
5848  // the streamer infos used by the value class to
5849  // be written to our output file.
5850  //
5851  if (fType == 3) {
5852  // -- TClonesArray, counter/master branch
5853  //
5854  // We must mark the streamer info for the
5855  // value class to be written to the file.
5856  //
5857  TClass* cl = fClonesClass;
5858  if (cl) {
5859  R__b.ForceWriteInfo(cl->GetStreamerInfo(), kTRUE);
5860  }
5861  }
5862  else if (fType == 4) {
5863  // -- STL container, counter/master branch
5864  //
5865  // We must mark the streamer info for the
5866  // value class to be written to the file.
5867  //
5868  TVirtualCollectionProxy* cp = GetCollectionProxy();
5869  if (cp) {
5870  TClass* cl = cp->GetValueClass();
5871  if (cl) {
5872  R__b.ForceWriteInfo(cl->GetStreamerInfo(), kTRUE);
5873  }
5874  }
5875  }
5876  // If we are in a separate file, then save
5877  // ourselves as an independent key.
5878  if (!dirsav) {
5879  // Note: No need to restore fDirectory, it was already zero.
5880  return;
5881  }
5882  if (!dirsav->IsWritable()) {
5883  fDirectory = dirsav;
5884  return;
5885  }
5886  TDirectory* pdirectory = fTree->GetDirectory();
5887  if (!pdirectory) {
5888  fDirectory = dirsav;
5889  return;
5890  }
5891  const char* treeFileName = pdirectory->GetFile()->GetName();
5892  TBranch* mother = GetMother();
5893  const char* motherFileName = treeFileName;
5894  if (mother && (mother != this)) {
5895  motherFileName = mother->GetFileName();
5896  }
5897  if ((fFileName.Length() > 0) && strcmp(motherFileName, fFileName.Data())) {
5898  dirsav->WriteTObject(this);
5899  }
5900  fDirectory = dirsav;
5901  }
5902 }
5903 
5904 
5905 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5906 /// Split class cl into sub-branches of this branch.
5907 ///
5908 /// This version of Unroll was formerly embedded in TTree::BronchExec
5909 /// It is moved here so we can make sure to call SetReadActionSequence.
5910 
5911 void TBranchElement::Unroll(const char *name, TClass *cl, TStreamerInfo *sinfo, char* objptr, Int_t bufsize, Int_t splitlevel)
5912 {
5913  //
5914  // Do we have a final dot in our name?
5915  //
5916 
5917  // Note: The branch constructor which takes a folder as input
5918  // creates top-level branch names with dots in them to
5919  // indicate the folder hierarchy.
5920  char* dot = (char*) strchr(name, '.');
5921  Int_t nch = strlen(name);
5922  Bool_t dotlast = kFALSE;
5923  if (nch && (name[nch-1] == '.')) {
5924  dotlast = kTRUE;
5925  }
5926 
5927  // Loop on all public data members of the class and its base classes and create branches for each one.
5928  TObjArray* blist = this->GetListOfBranches();
5929  TIter next(sinfo->GetElements());
5930  TStreamerElement* element = 0;
5931  TString bname;
5932  for (Int_t id = 0; (element = (TStreamerElement*) next()); ++id) {
5933  if (element->IsA() == TStreamerArtificial::Class()) {
5934  continue;
5935  }
5936  if (element->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kRepeat)) {
5937  continue;
5938  }
5939  if (element->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kCache) && !element->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kWrite)) {
5940  continue;
5941  }
5942  char* pointer = (char*) (objptr + element->GetOffset());
5943  // FIXME: This is not good enough, an STL container can be
5944  // a base, and the test will fail.
5945  // See TBranchElement::InitializeOffsets() for the
5946  // correct test.
5947  Bool_t isBase = (element->IsA() == TStreamerBase::Class());
5948  if (isBase) {
5949  TClass* clbase = element->GetClassPointer();
5950  if ((clbase == TObject::Class()) && cl->CanIgnoreTObjectStreamer()) {
5951  // Note: TStreamerInfo::Compile() leaves this element
5952  // out of the optimized info, although it does
5953  // exists in the non-compiled and non-optimized info.
5954  // FIXME: The test that TStreamerInfo::Compile() uses
5955  // is element->GetType() < 0, so that is what
5956  // we should do as well.
5957  continue;
5958  }
5959  if (clbase->GetListOfRealData()->GetSize() == 0) {
5960  // Do not create a branch for empty bases.
5961  continue;
5962  }
5963  }
5964  if (dot) {
5965  if (dotlast) {
5966  bname.Form("%s%s", name, element->GetFullName());
5967  } else {
5968  // FIXME: We are in the case where we have a top-level
5969  // branch name that was created by the branch
5970  // constructor which takes a folder as input.
5971  // The internal dots in the name are in place of
5972  // of the original slashes and represent the
5973  // folder hierarchy.
5974  if (isBase) {
5975  // FIXME: This is very strange, this is the only case where
5976  // we create a branch for a base class that does
5977  // not have the base class name in the branch name.
5978  // FIXME: This is also quite bad since classes with two
5979  // or more base classes end up with sub-branches
5980  // that have the same name.
5981  bname = name;
5982  } else {
5983  bname.Form("%s.%s", name, element->GetFullName());
5984  }
5985  }
5986  } else {
5987  // Note: For a base class element, this results in the branchname
5988  // being the name of the base class.
5989  bname.Form("%s", element->GetFullName());
5990  }
5991 
5992  if( splitlevel > TTree::kSplitCollectionOfPointers && element->GetClass() &&
5993  element->GetClass()->GetCollectionProxy() &&
5994  element->GetClass()->GetCollectionProxy()->HasPointers() )
5995  {
5996  TBranchSTL* brSTL = new TBranchSTL(this, bname, element->GetClass()->GetCollectionProxy(), bufsize, splitlevel-1, sinfo, id );
5997  blist->Add(brSTL);
5998  }
5999  else
6000  {
6001  TBranchElement* bre = new TBranchElement(this, bname, sinfo, id, pointer, bufsize, splitlevel - 1);
6002  bre->SetParentClass(cl);
6003  blist->Add(bre);
6004  }
6005  }
6006  // Now that we know that this branch is split, let's redo the actions.
6007  SetReadActionSequence();
6008  SetFillActionSequence();
6009 }
6010 
6011 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6012 /// Split class cl into sub-branches of this branch.
6013 ///
6014 /// Create a sub-branch of this branch for each non-empty,
6015 /// non-abstract base class of cl (unless we are a sub-branch
6016 /// of a TClonesArray or an STL container, in which case we
6017 /// do *not* create a sub-branch), and for each non-split data
6018 /// member of cl.
6019 ///
6020 /// Note: We do *not* create sub-branches for base classes of cl
6021 /// if we are a sub-branch of a TClonesArray or an STL container.
6022 ///
6023 /// Note: We do *not* create sub-branches for data members which
6024 /// have a class type and which we are splitting.
6025 ///
6026 /// Note: The above rules imply that the branch heirarchy increases
6027 /// in depth only for base classes of cl (unless we are inside
6028 /// of a TClonesArray or STL container, in which case the depth
6029 /// does *not* increase, the base class is elided) and for
6030 /// TClonesArray or STL container data members (which have one
6031 /// additional level of sub-branches). The only other way the
6032 /// depth increases is when the top-level branch has a split
6033 /// class data member, in that case the constructor will create
6034 /// a sub-branch for it. In other words, the interior nodes of
6035 /// the branch tree are all either: base class nodes; split
6036 /// class nodes which are direct sub-branches of top-level nodes
6037 /// (created by TClass::Bronch usually); or TClonesArray or STL
6038 /// container master nodes.
6039 ///
6040 /// Note: The exception to the above is for the top-level branches,
6041 /// Tree::Bronch creates nodes for everything in that case,
6042 /// except for a TObject base class of a class which has the
6043 /// can ignore tobject streamer flag set.
6044 
6045 Int_t TBranchElement::Unroll(const char* name, TClass* clParent, TClass* cl, char* ptr, Int_t basketsize, Int_t splitlevel, Int_t btype)
6046 {
6047  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6048  // Handling the case of STL collections of pointers
6049  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6050 
6051  Int_t splitSTLP = splitlevel - (splitlevel%TTree::kSplitCollectionOfPointers);
6052  splitlevel %= TTree::kSplitCollectionOfPointers;
6053 
6054  TString branchname;
6055 
6056  if ((cl == TObject::Class()) && clParent->CanIgnoreTObjectStreamer()) {
6057  return 0;
6058  }
6059 
6060  TStreamerInfo* sinfo = fTree->BuildStreamerInfo(cl);
6061 
6062  //
6063  // Do nothing if we couldn't build the streamer info for cl.
6064  //
6065 
6066  if (!sinfo) {
6067  return 0;
6068  }
6069 
6070  Int_t ndata = sinfo->GetNelement();
6071 
6072  if ((ndata == 1) && cl->GetCollectionProxy() && !strcmp(sinfo->GetElement(0)->GetName(), "This")) {
6073  // -- Class cl is an STL collection, refuse to split it.
6074  // Question: Why? We certainly could by switching to the value class.
6075  // Partial Answer: Only the branch element constructor can split STL containers.
6076  return 1;
6077  }
6078 
6079  for (Int_t elemID = 0; elemID < ndata; ++elemID) {
6080  // -- Loop over all the streamer elements and create sub-branches as needed.
6081  TStreamerElement* elem = sinfo->GetElement(elemID);
6082  if (elem->IsA() == TStreamerArtificial::Class()) {
6083  continue;
6084  }
6085  if (elem->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kRepeat)) {
6086  continue;
6087  }
6088  if (elem->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kCache) && !elem->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kWrite)) {
6089  continue;
6090  }
6091  Int_t offset = elem->GetOffset();
6092  // FIXME: An STL container as a base class gets TStreamerSTL as its class, so this test is not enough.
6093  // See InitializeOffsets() for the proper test.
6094  if (elem->IsA() == TStreamerBase::Class()) {
6095  // -- This is a base class of cl.
6096  TClass* clOfBase = elem->GetClassPointer();
6097  if (!clOfBase || ((clOfBase->Property() & kIsAbstract) && cl->InheritsFrom(TCollection::Class()))) {
6098  // -- Do nothing if we are one of the abstract collection (we know they have no data).
6099  return -1;
6100  }
6101  if ((btype == 31) || (btype == 41)) {
6102  // -- Elide the base-class sub-branches of a split TClonesArray or STL container.
6103  //
6104  // Note: We are eliding the base class here, that is, we never
6105  // create a branch for it, so the branch heirarchy is not
6106  // complete.
6107  // Note: The clParent parameter is the value class of the
6108  // container which we are splitting. It does not
6109  // appear in the branch heirarchy either.
6110  // Note: We can use parent class (clParent) != branch class (elemClass) to detection elision.
6111  Int_t unroll = -1;
6112  if (!elem->CannotSplit() || clOfBase == TObject::Class()) {
6113  unroll = Unroll(name, clParent, clOfBase, ptr + offset, basketsize, splitlevel+splitSTLP, btype);
6114  }
6115  if (unroll < 0) {
6116  // FIXME: We could not split because we are abstract, should we be doing this?
6117  if (strlen(name)) {
6118  branchname.Form("%s.%s", name, elem->GetFullName());
6119  } else {
6120  branchname.Form("%s", elem->GetFullName());
6121  }
6122  TBranchElement* branch = new TBranchElement(this, branchname, sinfo, elemID, 0, basketsize, 0, btype);
6123  branch->SetParentClass(clParent);
6124  fBranches.Add(branch);
6125  }
6126  } else if (clOfBase->GetListOfRealData()->GetSize()) {
6127  // -- Create a branch for a non-empty base class.
6128  if (strlen(name)) {
6129  branchname.Form("%s.%s", name, elem->GetFullName());
6130  // Elide the base class name when creating the sub-branches.
6131  // Note: The branch names for sub-branches of a base class branch
6132  // do not represent the full class heirarchy because we do
6133  // this, however it does keep the branch names for the
6134  // inherited data members simple.
6135  TBranchElement* branch = new TBranchElement(this, name, sinfo, elemID, ptr + offset, basketsize, splitlevel+splitSTLP, btype);
6136  // Then reset it to the proper name.
6137  branch->SetName(branchname);
6138  branch->SetTitle(branchname);
6139  branch->SetParentClass(clParent);
6140  fBranches.Add(branch);
6141  } else {
6142  branchname.Form("%s", elem->GetFullName());
6143  TBranchElement* branch = new TBranchElement(this, branchname, sinfo, elemID, ptr + offset, basketsize, splitlevel+splitSTLP, btype);
6144  branch->SetParentClass(clParent);
6145  fBranches.Add(branch);
6146  }
6147  }
6148  } else {
6149  // -- This is a data member of cl.
6150  if (strlen(name)) {
6151  branchname.Form("%s.%s", name, elem->GetFullName());
6152  } else {
6153  branchname.Form("%s", elem->GetFullName());
6154  }
6155  if ((splitlevel > 1) && ((elem->IsA() == TStreamerObject::Class()) || (elem->IsA() == TStreamerObjectAny::Class()))) {
6156  // -- We are splitting a non-TClonesArray (may inherit from TClonesArray though), non-STL container object.
6157  //
6158  // Ignore an abstract class.
6159  // FIXME: How could an abstract class get here?
6160  // Partial answer: It is a base class. But this is a data member!
6161  TClass* elemClass = elem->GetClassPointer();
6162  if (!elemClass || elemClass->Property() & kIsAbstract) {
6163  return -1;
6164  }
6165  if (elem->CannotSplit()) {
6166  // We are not splitting.
6167  TBranchElement* branch = new TBranchElement(this, branchname, sinfo, elemID, ptr + offset, basketsize, 0, btype);
6168  branch->SetParentClass(clParent);
6169  fBranches.Add(branch);
6170  } else if (elemClass->InheritsFrom(TClonesArray::Class())) {
6171  // Splitting something derived from TClonesArray.
6172  Int_t subSplitlevel = splitlevel-1;
6173  if (btype == 31 || btype == 41 || elem->CannotSplit()) {
6174  // -- We split the sub-branches of a TClonesArray or an STL container only once.
6175  subSplitlevel = 0;
6176  }
6177  TBranchElement* branch = new TBranchElement(this, branchname, sinfo, elemID, ptr + offset, basketsize, subSplitlevel, btype);
6178  branch->SetParentClass(clParent);
6179  fBranches.Add(branch);
6180  } else {
6181  // Splitting a normal class.
6182  // FIXME: We are eliding the class we are splitting here,
6183  // i.e., we do not create a branch for it, so the
6184  // branch heirarchy does not match the class heirarchy.
6185  // Note: clParent is the class which contains a data member of
6186  // the class type which we are splitting.
6187  // Note: We can use parent class (clParent) != branch class (elemClass) to detection elision.
6188  Int_t unroll = Unroll(branchname, clParent, elemClass, ptr + offset, basketsize, splitlevel-1+splitSTLP, btype);
6189  if (unroll < 0) {
6190  // FIXME: We could not split because we are abstract, should we be doing this?
6191  TBranchElement* branch = new TBranchElement(this, branchname, sinfo, elemID, ptr + offset, basketsize, 0, btype);
6192  branch->SetParentClass(clParent);
6193  fBranches.Add(branch);
6194  }
6195  }
6196  }
6197  else if( elem->GetClassPointer() &&
6198  elem->GetClassPointer()->GetCollectionProxy() &&
6199  elem->GetClassPointer()->GetCollectionProxy()->HasPointers() &&
6200  splitSTLP && fType != 4 )
6201  {
6202 
6203  TBranchSTL* branch = new TBranchSTL( this, branchname,
6204  elem->GetClassPointer()->GetCollectionProxy(),
6205  basketsize, splitlevel - 1+splitSTLP, sinfo, elemID );
6206  branch->SetAddress( ptr+offset );
6207  fBranches.Add( branch );
6208  }
6209  else if ((elem->IsA() == TStreamerSTL::Class()) && !elem->IsaPointer()) {
6210  // -- We have an STL container.
6211  // Question: What if splitlevel == 0 here?
6212  // Answer: then we should not be here.
6213  Int_t subSplitlevel = splitlevel - 1;
6214  if ((btype == 31) || (btype == 41) || elem->CannotSplit()) {
6215  // -- We split the sub-branches of a TClonesArray or an STL container only once.
6216  subSplitlevel = 0;
6217  }
6218  TBranchElement* branch = new TBranchElement(this, branchname, sinfo, elemID, ptr + offset, basketsize, subSplitlevel+splitSTLP, btype);
6219  branch->SetParentClass(clParent);
6220  fBranches.Add(branch);
6221  } else if (((btype != 31) && (btype != 41)) && ptr && ((elem->GetClassPointer() == TClonesArray::Class()) || ((elem->IsA() == TStreamerSTL::Class()) && !elem->CannotSplit()))) {
6222  // -- We have a TClonesArray.
6223  // FIXME: We could get a ptr to a TClonesArray here by mistake.
6224  // Question: What if splitlevel == 0 here?
6225  // Answer: then we should not be here.
6226  // Note: ptr may be null in case of a TClonesArray inside another
6227  // TClonesArray or STL container, see the else clause.
6228  TBranchElement* branch = new TBranchElement(this, branchname, sinfo, elemID, ptr + offset, basketsize, splitlevel-1+splitSTLP, btype);
6229  branch->SetParentClass(clParent);
6230  fBranches.Add(branch);
6231  } else {
6232  // -- We are not going to split this element any farther.
6233  TBranchElement* branch = new TBranchElement(this, branchname, sinfo, elemID, 0, basketsize, splitSTLP, btype);
6234  branch->SetType(btype);
6235  branch->SetParentClass(clParent);
6236  fBranches.Add(branch);
6237  }
6238  }
6239  }
6240 
6241  if (!fBranches.IsEmpty()) {
6242  // Refresh this branch's action now that we know whether it is split or not.
6243  SetReadActionSequence();
6244  SetFillActionSequence();
6245  }
6246  return 1;
6247 }
6248 
6249 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6250 /// Refresh the value of fDirectory (i.e. where this branch writes/reads its buffers)
6251 /// with the current value of fTree->GetCurrentFile unless this branch has been
6252 /// redirected to a different file. Also update the sub-branches.
6253 
6254 void TBranchElement::UpdateFile()
6255 {
6256  // The BranchCount and BranchCount2 are part of higher level branches' list of
6257  // branches.
6258  // if (fBranchCount) fBranchCount->UpdateFile();
6259  // if (fBranchCount2) fBranchCount2->UpdateFile();
6260  TBranch::UpdateFile();
6261 }
